---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';
import ClusterFunnelBlock from '@/components/chrome/ClusterFunnelBlock.astro';
import { buildBreadcrumb } from '@/lib/seo';

const breadcrumb = buildBreadcrumb([
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'About', url: '/about/' },
]);
---
<Layout
  title="About — The STR Ledger"
  description="Excel workbooks and PDF guides for short-term rental operators. The hub of a five-site toolkit covering acquisition, math, ops, guests, and operator manuals."
  path="/about"
  jsonLd={breadcrumb}
>
  <article class="bg-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-12 pb-9 prose">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-h1 text-navy leading-tight">
        About The STR Ledger<span class="period-gold">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lead text-ink-2">
        <em>Run your rentals before they run you.</em>
      </p>

      <h2>What this is</h2>
      <p>
        The STR Ledger publishes Excel workbooks and PDF guides for short-term rental operators. Schedule E-ready bookkeeping. Turnover ops. Pricing math. Acquisition underwriting. Built for hosts who run 3-10 properties as a real business — not a hobby.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this exists</h2>
      <p>
        QuickBooks doesn't understand cleaning fees. Generic tax software doesn't understand a Schedule E with cost segregation. AirDNA is a market data tool, not a bookkeeping system. The Ledger fills the gap between "spreadsheet you cobbled together" and "enterprise PMS you don't need."
      </p>

      <h2>The full toolkit</h2>
      <p>
        The STR Ledger is the hub. Five sister sites cover the free math, ops generators, and operator manuals that pair with the paid workbooks:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://strbuyers.tools">strbuyers.tools</a> — free pre-buy tools: DSCR, market score, comp analysis.</li>
        <li><a href="https://strhost.tools">strhost.tools</a> — free calculators: fees, profit, RevPAR, break-even, lodging tax.</li>
        <li><a href="https://strops.tools">strops.tools</a> — free ops tools: turnover, dispatch, smart locks.</li>
        <li><a href="https://strguests.tools">strguests.tools</a> — free generators: house rules, welcome books, AI replies.</li>
        <li><a href="https://strmanuals.com">strmanuals.com</a> — paid operator manuals and SOP packs.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The free tools cover the math. The workbooks cover the part you take to your CPA.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we build for</h2>
      <p>
        Semi-Pro Sarah: 38-55, married to a W2 partner, 3-10 STR properties, runs the portfolio as the real business. HHI $200K+, STR gross $150K-500K/year. Top pains: tax season anxiety, cleaner chaos, pricing guesswork, the partner asking "where are the real books?"
      </p>
      <p>
        If that's you, the workbooks were drafted with your portfolio in mind.
      </p>

      <h2>What this is not</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Not a SaaS. No accounts, no monthly subscription, no dashboard you have to learn.</li>
        <li>Not tax advice. The workbooks compute numbers; your CPA files your return.</li>
        <li>Not a PMS. We don't talk to Airbnb's API. We're the bookkeeping math layer.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:hello@thestrledger.com" class="font-mono">hello@thestrledger.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <ClusterFunnelBlock />
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose :global(h2) { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--t-h2-size, 36px); color: var(--brand-navy); margin-top: var(--sp-7); margin-bottom: var(--sp-3); line-height: 1.1; }
  .prose :global(p) { color: var(--fg-1); margin-bottom: var(--sp-3); line-height: 1.6; }
  .prose :global(ul) { margin: var(--sp-3) 0 var(--sp-4); padding-left: var(--sp-5); }
  .prose :global(li) { margin-bottom: var(--sp-2); line-height: 1.55; }
  .prose :global(a) { color: var(--brand-navy); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: var(--brand-gold); text-underline-offset: 3px; }
</style>
